-- Markets Expert Buch May Become Merkel Economic Adviser, FTD Says
-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 2012-02-06T08:25:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/markets-expert-buch-may-become-merkel-economic-adviser-ftd-says.html
Claudia Buch, a professor at
Tuebingen University and specialist on financial markets, is the
favorite to fill an opening on German Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s
council of economic advisers, the Financial Times Deutschland
reported, without saying how it got the information.  Merkel’s government is seeking a replacement for Beatrice Weder di Mauro, who gave notice of her resignation from the
panel on Feb. 3, the German newspaper reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Czuczka in Berlin at 
